I noticed there's this line of code in the base.html file:

{# This is intended to be used if a template requires template specific style sheets #}
    {% if template_css %}
      {{ require_css(get_asset_url(template_css)) }}
    {% endif %}

How do we use this? I can't find any documentation on this. I want to insert a CSS file just for a specific template.

Hmm. I put it in my file like this

{% set template_css = "../css/lp.css" %}
{% extends "./layouts/base.html" %}

I also tried putting the extends first ... neither seem to be loading my css file.

```{% set template_css = "../css/lp.css" %}
{% extends "./layouts/base.html" %}

{% block body %} 

&lt;html markup goes here&gt;
{% endblock %}```
